After almost two years, the light commercial vehicle market is starting to see some light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9,425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decrease, according to figures from the employers' union of manufacturers Anfac and Ganvam, that of dealers.
The good news, however, is that the benchmark for comparison in November 2008 was particularly poor, with a decrease of 60% compared to the previous year.
