How much should you be paid based on your Facebook profile?
Facebook users can know the salary they would deserve based on their profile, thanks to a new app from Trovit, the search engine with the highest number of real estate classifieds, jobs and vehicles in Spain.
The “How much should you be paid?” tool calculates users’ salaries from more than 140,000 job offers Trovit has in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where you must register your profession, your years of experience, your age and the city where you want to work.
For the past week that the app has been running, the search engine has detected that as a rule, the Spanish worker “feels poorly paid,” explained in a statement Trovit’s product manager, Albert Ribera.
According to data Trovit has from its search engines in the UK and France, Spaniards are the lowest paid.
A British computer programmer receives 45,226 euros gross annually and a French one, 31,059, while a Spanish one receives 24,000 euros.
Similarly, a driver receives 34,247 euros gross annually in England, 25,751 in France and 16,420 in Spain.
According to Trovit, the lowest paid job in Spain is that of server, with 11,592 euros net annual, followed by that of seller, with 14,725 euros, and that of worker, with 15,667 euros.
The most sought-after jobs on the Internet in the past three months have been as a driver, part-time jobs and social worker.
